CIViC Description: While loss-of-function events in TP53 are very common in cancer, the R248 variants seem not only to result in loss of tumor-suppression, but also act as a gain-of-function mutation that can promote tumorigenesis in mouse models. This mutant is also more responsive to treatment with doxorubicin than its wild-type counterparts. While the prognostic impact of individual TP53 mutations is influenced by the cohort being studied, R248 mutations have been shown to confer worse overall survival.
